article.headline: Portland St. 83, Northern Arizona 78
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Juma Kamara scored a career high 25 points to lead Portland State to an 83-78 win over Northern Arizona on Saturday night. Dupree Lucas had 19 points for Portland State (4-4, 13-8) and Scott Morrison added 12 points for the Vikings. Stephen Sir led Northern Arizona (5-3, 10-9) with 21 points. Ruben Boykin, Jr. had 17 and Tyrone Bazy scored 16 points for the Lumberjacks. Trailing 60-59 with just under 12 minutes left to play, Portland State rattled off an 8-1 run and led 67-61 after Lucas hit two free throws. The Vikings held the lead the rest of the way despite making just one field goal the final six minutes of the game. NAU managed to close within two points down the stretch but Kamara sealed the victory with two free throws with 30 seconds left to play. Portland State shot 52 percent for the game, including 50 percent from 3-point range.
